Tuesday night was the annual ROP Award of Excellence ceremony. 10 of our Bulldogs were recognized at this event. ALL ROP students are required to complete a portfolio and attend an interview with a member of the business community. ROP teachers then select a student from their class based on the portfolio interview and class participation for this award. Below is a list of the Bulldogs who were chosen for this outstanding accomplishment! If you have any of these students in class or see them on campus, make sure to congratulate them for a job well done! Thanks

post_text:
Attention Bulldogs!!!

We're one day shy of our CIF-SJS D5 basketball playoff game against Sierra Ridge Rite of Passage, out of San Andreas, CA. (Wednesday, 7 p.m., LGHS). The No. 10-seeded Rams come in at 15-7 overall. The Rams beat Mariposa by 10 in December. That's the only opponent they share with our No. 7-seeded Le Grand Bulldogs (10-10), which sailed into the playoffs by going 8-3 in the last 11 games. Come back tonight to hear our varsity Bulldogs break down the 2011-12 season and their playoff matchup in 12 questions or less. Let's go, Bulldogs!

Also don't forget the school is giving away free pizza to the first 50 students that come to the game!!!

See you there!

post_text: VARSITY BOYS BEAT MARIPOSA---POSTGAME NOTES---The 71-59 victory was the first for LG at Mariposa since 2004 and the first at Mariposa for Alvarez as LG coach ... Zach Moreno scored 30 points with Miguel Chavez and Mauricio Contreras adding 13 each ... AJ Salcido (9), Aaron Mendoza (8) and The rest of the backcourt did great work on defense, forcing turnovers and releasing again and again for transition layups ... Le Grand advances to the CIF-SJS playoffs. We find out Sunday against which team and where. Stay tuned!!!
